node.text: Super Absorbent Polymer: poly-acrylamide polymer crystals are able to absorb up to 200 times their volume of water. Here seven small spheres, approximately 4mm in diameter, were immersed in water for three hours, after which they were slightly more than 23mm across. The final gel sphere is more than 99.5% water- and they bounce! ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for info on where to get these and other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #physics #physicsfun #physicstoy #polyacrylamide #absorbent #hydrophilic #watergel #watergelcrystals #chemistry #physicstoy #density #science #scienceisawesome

Equatorial Bulge Demo: two springy circular rings flatten along their axis of rotation in proportion to the rate of spin in this classic teaching demonstration. This device demonstrates that centripetal accelerations applied to an elastic sphere will cause it to bulge at the equator- becoming an oblate spheroid.  Isaac Newton predicted that given the Earth’s rotation, the radius to the equator would be larger than the radius to the North Pole by 1 part in 230. He was correct! (although overestimated slightly- swipe for description) Modern measurements indicate 1 part in 294.7. Question: At what location on Earth could you stand on land and be furtherest from its center? Mt Everest is a good guess, but the correct answer is the top of Mt Chimborazo in Ecuador. (swipe twice for details) Although Everest is higher above sea level, the equatorial bulge puts the top of Chimborazo a 2.2 km further into space from the center of the Earth. ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for more info and details on where to get many of the amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #physics #physicsfun #physicstoy #physicsdemo #oblatesphereoid #equator #equitorialbulge #chimborazo #everest #centripetal #angularmomentum #centripetalacceleration #science #rotatingearth #scienceisawesome

node.text: The Square Wave: one of my favorite interactive kinetic sculptures from the mind of artist Ivan Black. Waves propagate through the 24 interlocking right angle metal rods, folding the structure into a tight curl- and a reverse snap will bring it back to the initial flat square state. An important design feature is that each right angle rod is limited to move through about 45 degrees, and all through parallel axes, allowing for the beautiful rotational wave motion via a cascade of angular momentum transfer. See other amazing creations by Ivan on his IG stream: @ivanblacksculpture ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for info to purchase a Square Wave and find other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #kineticart #angularmomentum #physicstoy #physics #rotation #squarewave #rotationalinertia #physicsfun #art #science #scienceisawesome

node.text: The Orb Drop IV: @orbdrop has created another fun DIY marble run- this one uses an Archimedean screw mechanism to bring the marbles continuously back to the top where they are launched along one of three paths- including a vortex funnel. Gravitational potential energy is transformed to the kinetic energy of the orbs as they loop and negotiate the banked turns of the snaking tracks. Three AA batteries and a small motor power the transport assembly. ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for more info and where to get this Orb Drop kit and other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #physics #physicstoy #gravity #gravitywell #orbdrop #angularmomentum #kinetic #kineticart #kineticenergy #marblerun #science #scienceisawesome

node.text: The FluoroSphere: intricate and dynamic lights shows are produced within an elegant glass sphere as fluorescent dyes in mineral oil slowly mix into room temperature water. Ultraviolet LEDs (in the base on which the sphere rests) make the dyes glow brightly and reveal the initial nondiffusive mixing structure which includes the phenomena of drops, plumes, and other features of Rayleigh-Taylor instabilities. Shown here, slightly sped up, is the first 8 minutes or so of the process which takes up to half an hour to mix evenly. The green light is characteristic of the famous fluorescein dye. ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for info on where to get this science kit and other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #physics #physicsfun #physicstoy #fluorescent #fluorescence #quantummechanics #stokesshift #fluorescein #viscosity #viscousflow #reynoldsnumber #rayleightaylorinstability #mixing #polymer #turbulence #science #scienceisawesome

node.text: Dymaxion Map: today some math fun with this unique mapping of the Earth where the globe is projected onto an icosahedron and then unfolded onto two dimensions. Invented by the famous architect R. Buckminster Fuller, the Dymaxion projection map is designed such that it does not have a “right way up” and showing the continents as “one island Earth”. This mapping also produces less distortion of relative areas and shapes- note here that Greenland looks, correctly, much smaller than Africa- unlike what is seen on many world maps where they look the same size. This version, designed by Brendan Ravenhill, uses flat magnets to allow a very satisfying transformation between the flat 2D net and the 3D icosahedron “globe”. ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for more info on where to get this map and other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #map #earth #globe #cartography #projection #mapprojection #buckminsterfuller #dymaxion #geometry #platonicsolid #icosahedron #physics #physicstoy #physicsfun #science #mathtoy #mathstoy #scienceisawesome

node.text: Diffractive Optical Element: images produced by constructive and deconstructive interference of coherent laser light. The patches of microstructure on the surface of this transparent plastic are far field holograms- transmission holograms, but with the image at infinity. Side by side images from two different laser wavelengths (red 635 nm, green 520 nm) shows clearly the red image is larger than the green since diffraction angle is proportional the wavelength. So much physics here! ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for info on where to obtain this device and many other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #holidayspecs #holospecs #transmissionhologram #hologram #holographic #earth #physics #physicstoy #diffraction #laser #optics #diffractiveopticalelement #science #constructiveinterference #encoding #scienceisawesome

node.text: Tea-Light Floating Engine: a candle powered super simple steam engine. The engine is just a coil of copper tubing, filled with water. The ends of the tube are bent and directed to produce counter-clockwise rotation. Steam builds up pushing water out with an explosive jet- which then results in a partial vacuum in the coil which pulls more water in to repeat the process. The water expulsion is in the form of jet directed out the end of the tube whereas the refill comes back in to the tube from a larger range of angles- so on balance the engine moves opposite to the direction of the jets. ➡️ Follow the link in my profile for info on where to get this simple engine kit and other amazing items featured here on @physicsfun #engine #physics #thermodynamics #physicstoy #physicsfun #steamengine #phasechange  #poppopboat #science #tealight #scienceisawesome #candle #heatengine
